flow, short circuit, stability, EMT analysis Updated network upgrade cost assignment | | | |\n\nCluster Study Process *ISO will request a independent entity variation to allow 270 days for the completion of the Cluster Study\n\nCluster Study Process, continued\n\nOrder No. 2023 Requirements (see graphic on previous slide) ISO’s Proposed Approach\n\n• Cluster Request Window \n• Cluster Engagement Window \n• Cluster Study \n• Cluster Restudy \n• Adopt these changes with the following \nexceptions: \n• ISO will request 270 calendar days \n(instead of the Order’s 150 CDs) to \ncomplete the Cluster Study \n• Consistent with established \ntimeline for System Impact Studies \nin New England \n• Establish a uniform study deposit \namount of $250,000*, consistent with \nexisting New England LGIP requirements \n• ISO anticipates opening the first Cluster \nRequest Window in mid-2025 \n• After the completion of the Transitional \nCluster Study \n\n*Independent entity variation Order No. 2023 proposes study deposits that vary with Generating Facility size\n\nCluster Study Cycle\n\nCustomer \nRequest Window \n• 45 Calendar Days \n(CDs) \n\nCustomer Engagement Window •60 CDs\n\nCluster Study •270 CDs\n\nCluster Study Results and Customer Commitments •40 CDs\n\nCluster Restudy (if needed) •150 CDs\n\nFacilities Study •90 or 180 CDs\n\nFacility Study Results and Comment Period •60 CDs\n\nInterconnection Agreement Phase •75 CDs\n\n...\n\n460 day study window\n\nSubsequent Clusters\n\n| Customer | | Customer | Cluster Study | Cluster Study | | | Cluster | | | Facilities | | | Facility Study | | Interconnecti | | | | | | |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Request | | Engagement | | Results and | | | Restudy (if | | | Study | | | Results and | | on Agreement | | | | | | |\n| Window | | Window | | Customer | | | needed) | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |\n| | | | | Commitments | | | | | |